title: Become a school or college governor

heading_context: Become a school or college governor
chunks.html_content:
Apply online to register your interest in becoming a school governor.

You can also apply directly to your local school.
chunks.plain_content:
Become a school or college governor
Apply online to register your interest in becoming a school governor.
You can also apply directly to your local school.

heading_context: Become a school or college governor
chunks.html_content: Contact your local further education college directly to become a college governor.
chunks.plain_content:
Become a school or college governor
Contact your local further education college directly to become a college governor.

heading_context: Become a school or college governor
chunks.html_content:
You must be aged 18 or over to become a school governor. There’s no minimum age to be a student governor of a further education college.

As a governor, you can:

  • help the school or college with its strategy
  • hold the headteacher, principal or CEO to account for a school or college’s performance
  • make sure the school or college budget is properly managed

Find out more about becoming a school governor.

heading_context: Become a school or college governor
chunks.html_content: You can only apply online in England. If you live in Scotland or Wales contact your local council instead. Find out about becoming a governor in Northern Ireland.
